Thorax blackish brown with whitish gray pollen. Mesoscutum with 0+ 3 dc (anterior dc clearly behind transverse scutal suture), acr in 8 somewhat irregular rows; prsc shorter than 1 st post–sutural dc . Anepisternum blackish except yellow ventroapical corner, and katepisternum blackish brown with whitish gray pollen. Scutellum brownish black except yellow apical margin, with whitish gray pollen. Legs pale yellow except tarsomere 5 brown on apical 1 / 2 ; hind tibia with an incomplete brown basal ring. Fore femur with 3–4 strong pv and 5–6 pd , ctenidium with 12–14 short bristles; fore tibia with 1 long preapical ad and 1 short apv . Mid femur with 6 a and 1 apv ; mid tibia with 1 strong preapical ad and 3 strong apv . Hind femur with 1 preapical ad ; hind tibia with 1 weak preapical ad and 1 short apv . Wing (
Fig. 1
) slightly yellow, only with a narrow brown stripe on dm-cu ; subcostal cell hyaline; costa with 2 nd (between R 1 and R 2 + 3 ), 3 rd (between R 2 + 3 and R 4 + 5 ) and 4 th (between R 4 + 5 and M 1 ) sections in proportion of 1.5 mm : 0.6 mm : 0.3 mm ; rm at middle of discal cell; ultimate and penultimate sections of M 1 in proportion of 1.1 mm : 1.2 mm ; ultimate section of CuA 1 about 1 / 5 of penultimate. Halter pale yellow.

Abdomen yellow with sparse silvery white pollen; tergite 2 with a pair of blackish brown lateral bands; tergites 3–5 each with a blackish brown posterior band, and an indistinct triangular median spot confluent with the blackish brown posterior band; tergite 6 without spot. Male genitalia (
Figs. 12–16
): protandrium circular; epandrium nearly rectangular, with a row of apical hairs in lateral view, surstylus narrow incurved stick–like in lateral view and bifurcated in ventral view; hypandrium with a pair of short bar–like ventral process, gonopod columniform, slightly curved; aedeagus with a small apical incision, a pair of dorsal sclerites and dorsoapical teeth.
